## `ensureArray()` ‚Äî Always Use in Render Functions
```javascript
function ensureArray(value) {
    if (Array.isArray(value)) return value;
    if (value && typeof value === 'object') return Object.values(value);
    return [];
}
```

## `toTitleCase()` ‚Äî Module-Level Helper
`toTitleCase` is defined at module scope (right after `ensureArray`) and must **not** be redeclared inside any render function:
```javascript
/** @param {string} s @returns {string} */
function toTitleCase(s) {
    return s ? s.replace(/\w\S*/g, t => t.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + t.slice(1).toLowerCase()) : s;
}
```
Use it for any LLM-returned enum-like string that should appear in title case: `employment_type`, `work_arrangement`, priority labels, etc. Always pair with `decodeEntities()` for fields that came from the server: `toTitleCase(decodeEntities(value))`.

## `escapeHtml()` ‚Äî Decode `&amp;` First, Then Named Entities
`ui/src/pages/application-detail.ts` uses the decode-first pattern. **Decode order matters**: `&amp;` must be decoded before `&#x27;` / `&#039;` so that bleach's double-encoded `&amp;#x27;` is correctly resolved to `'`. Wrong order leaves `&#x27;` displaying literally as text in `innerHTML`.

See `frontend-js-strict.mdc` ¬ß1 for the canonical implementation.

## `decodeEntities()` ‚Äî For `.textContent` Fields
`renderHeader()` assigns job title and company name via `.textContent`, which does not interpret HTML entities. Always use `decodeEntities(str)` (decode-only, no re-encode) for these assignments, never raw server-rendered strings.

**Unknown employer ‚Äî `isPlaceholderCompanyName()`**  
The API may store a **non-empty** placeholder (`‚Äî`, `-`, `N/A`, `unknown`, etc.) when no employer is named. Those strings are truthy in JavaScript, so always gate the company line with **`isPlaceholderCompanyName(job.company_name)`** (inverse of backend **`_has_usable_company_name()`** in `agents/company_research.py`). When the name is missing or a placeholder, `#companyName` must show **`Unknown`** ‚Äî never the literal word ‚ÄúCompany‚Äù, a bare dash, or raw LLM punctuation.

```javascript
if (jtEl) jtEl.textContent = decodeEntities(job.job_title || 'Job Application');
if (cnEl) {
  const companyTrimmed = job.company_name && String(job.company_name).trim();
  cnEl.textContent =
    companyTrimmed && !isPlaceholderCompanyName(job.company_name)
      ? decodeEntities(companyTrimmed)
      : 'Unknown';
}
```

**Company tab heading** ‚Äî Use `About ${escapeHtml(effectiveCompanyName)}` when a usable employer name exists; otherwise **`About this opportunity`**. Effective name resolution lives in `ui/src/application-detail/render-overview.ts` (`resolveEffectiveCompanyName`).

**Company research notices** (`ui/src/application-detail/render-overview.ts`) ‚Äî Before the About section, show at most one `.company-research-notice`:

| Condition | Banner |
|-----------|--------|
| Recruiting/staffing agency labeled while analyzer company is a placeholder | **Posted by {agency} (recruiting agency).** Actual hiring employer not named. |
| `research_quality === 'uncertain'` or `confidence_assessment.overall_confidence === 'LOW'` | **Company research may not match this employer.** |
| `research_quality === 'posting_only'` | **Employer not named in this posting.** Role/industry guidance only. |

Backend fields: `employer_type`, `research_quality`, `confidence_assessment` (see **`agent-patterns.mdc`**).

**View posting link ‚Äî `#jobUrlMeta` / `#jobUrlLink`**  
When `data.job_url` is a valid http(s) URL, `renderHeader()` sets `jobUrlLink.href` and removes `.is-hidden` from `#jobUrlMeta`. Template: `<a id="jobUrlLink" ‚Ä¶ rel="noopener noreferrer">View posting</a>`. Same `/^https?:\/\//` guard as company website links ‚Äî hide the meta row when missing or invalid.

**Location line ‚Äî primary + `additional_locations`**  
Many postings list multiple offices. Job Analyzer stores extras in **`job.additional_locations`** (`List[str]`). Header `#jobLocation` and Job Details render:

```javascript
const _extraLocations = Array.isArray(job.additional_locations) ? job.additional_locations.filter(Boolean) : [];
const _primaryLocation = [job.job_city, job.job_state, job.job_country].filter(Boolean).join(', ');
const location = [_primaryLocation, ..._extraLocations].filter(Boolean).join(' | ');
```

Profile Matcher uses all offered locations when judging location fit (see **`agent-patterns.mdc`**).

