## Your Fit Tab ‚Äî Data Field Mapping
Source: `match` object from `ProfileMatchingResult`

| Section | Fields |
|---------|--------|
| Apply Decision Banner | `match.executive_summary.{should_apply, priority_level, success_probability, confidence}` |
| Verdict Card | `match.executive_summary.{fit_assessment, recommendation}` |
| Qualification Breakdown | `match.qualification_breakdown` + `skill_gaps_analysis`, `career_trajectory`. **Do NOT render a trajectory badge (`ASCENDING`/`LATERAL`/`DESCENDING`) inline with the Experience row label** ‚Äî the score bar and description already convey fit quality clearly. |
| Competitive Position | `match.competitive_positioning.{estimated_percentile, unique_value_proposition, strengths_vs_typical_applicant, weaknesses_vs_typical_applicant}` |
| Salary Fit | If `salaryF.assessment === 'UNKNOWN'` ‚Üí show "N/A ‚Äî salary not listed" instead of a score |
| Percentile bar | Has a `.percentile-marker` dot. Position is set via `data-pct` attribute + JS after `innerHTML` assignment ‚Äî do NOT use `style="left: X%"` inside the HTML string (the property is not reliably applied when set inside dynamically injected HTML). |
| Employer Concerns | `match.red_flags_for_employer` ‚Äî amber `fa-minus-circle` icons (not red `fa-times-circle`). Section label: **"Potential Employer Concerns"** (not "What the Employer Might Worry About") |

### Percentile Marker ‚Äî Set Position via JS After innerHTML
The `.percentile-marker` dot position **must** be set in JavaScript after the `innerHTML` assignment, using `data-pct`:
```javascript
// Inside the HTML string:
`<div class="percentile-marker" data-pct="${Math.min(percentile, 100)}"></div>`
// After innerHTML:
const marker = fcEl.querySelector('.percentile-marker[data-pct]');
if (marker) marker.style.left = marker.dataset['pct'] + '%';
```
Do NOT use `style="left: X%"` inside the HTML string ‚Äî browsers may not reliably apply `left` when the element is created via `innerHTML` injection.

