## Content Regeneration Endpoints
```
POST /api/v1/workflow/generate-documents/{session_id}        # on-demand (analysis_complete apps); generates cover letter + resume advisor together
POST /api/v1/workflow/regenerate-cover-letter/{session_id}   # rate: 5/hour; allowed for completed, awaiting_confirmation, analysis_complete
POST /api/v1/workflow/regenerate-resume/{session_id}         # rate: 5/hour; allowed for completed, awaiting_confirmation, analysis_complete
POST /api/v1/workflow/continue/{session_id}                  # resume workflow from awaiting_confirmation (triggers company + cover + resume)
POST /api/v1/interview-prep/{session_id}/generate            # rate: 5/hour; allowed for completed, awaiting_confirmation, analysis_complete
GET  /api/v1/interview-prep/{session_id}                     # get prep
GET  /api/v1/interview-prep/{session_id}/status              # poll status
POST /api/v1/hiring-outreach/{session_id}/generate           # rate: 5/hour; requires job_analysis + BYOK
GET  /api/v1/hiring-outreach/{session_id}                    # get outreach
GET  /api/v1/hiring-outreach/{session_id}/status             # poll status
DELETE /api/v1/hiring-outreach/{session_id}                  # delete outreach
```

All three regeneration endpoints (`regenerate-cover-letter`, `regenerate-resume`, `generate-interview-prep`) accept the statuses: `completed`, `awaiting_confirmation`, **and `analysis_complete`** ‚Äî not just `completed`. This is intentional: users on all three states can trigger or re-trigger content generation.

## Workflow Status ‚Äî `workflowStatus` Module Variable
`ui/src/pages/application-detail.ts` stores the current workflow status in a module-level `workflowStatus` string (populated by `loadApplicationData()` from `statusData.status`). Render functions use this to detect gate-stopped applications:
```javascript
let workflowStatus = '';
// In loadApplicationData():
workflowStatus = statusData.status || '';
```

Dashboard display mapping (set in `api/workflow.py` sync endpoint):
| Workflow status | App card status shown |
|---|---|
| `completed` | COMPLETED |
| `awaiting_confirmation` | **COMPLETED** (not PROCESSING ‚Äî analysis is fully done) |
| `analysis_complete` | COMPLETED |
| `in_progress` / `initialized` | PROCESSING |
| `failed` | FAILED |

## Generate Button ‚Äî `analysis_complete` Applications

Four generation scenarios:
1. **Auto-generate ON + above gate** ‚Üí both docs created automatically by workflow
2. **Auto-generate ON + below gate** ‚Üí workflow stops at `awaiting_confirmation`, no docs
3. **Auto-generate OFF** ‚Üí workflow ends at `analysis_complete`, no docs ever created
4. **Manual trigger** ‚Üí user clicks individual button in each tab to generate that doc only

For scenarios 2 and 4, **each tab has its own independent "Generate" button** that calls `generateSingle()`. Never combine them unless the user explicitly asks to generate both.

### `generateSingle(which, btn)`
Generates a single document (cover letter **or** resume tips) without touching the other:
```javascript
async function generateSingle(which, btn) {
    const endpoint = which === 'cover'
        ? `${API_BASE}/workflow/regenerate-cover-letter/${currentSessionId}`
        : `${API_BASE}/workflow/regenerate-resume/${currentSessionId}`;
    // Sets btn.disabled + btn.classList.add('loading'), POSTs, then loadApplicationData()
}
```

### Empty State Pattern (Cover Letter and Resume tabs)
Both empty-state render blocks use `regen-btn` style (not `btn-primary`). **Do NOT add an icon inside `<span class="btn-text">`** ‚Äî the four generate buttons are icon-free:
```javascript
// Cover Letter tab
`<div class="empty-state">
  <i class="fas fa-envelope empty-state-icon"></i>
  <p class="empty-state-title">Cover Letter</p>
  <p class="empty-state-desc">‚Ä¶reason‚Ä¶</p>
  <button class="regen-btn" data-action="gen-cover">
    <span class="spinner"></span>
    <span class="btn-text">Generate Cover Letter</span>
  </button>
</div>`
// Resume tab ‚Äî same pattern, data-action="gen-resume", btn-text "Generate Resume Tips"
// Interview tab ‚Äî data-action="gen-interview", btn-text "Generate Interview Prep"
// Company tab continue button ‚Äî btn-text "Run Full Analysis Anyway"
```
Event is bound via `data-action` delegation in the pane's `addEventListener('click')` block ‚Äî never inline `onclick`.

